FBIS4-6175 "dreas075_h_94002" FBIS-EAS-94-075 Daily Report 19 Apr 1994 Brunei, Malaysia & Singapore Malaysia Czech Foreign Minister Pays Official Visit Czech Foreign Minister Pays Official Visit Meets With Trade Minister BK1904094894 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0800 GMT 19 Apr 94 BK1904094894 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia English BFN [Text] Malaysia is a gateway to ASEAN with the 350 million people in its dynamic region. The country is also a gateway to the whole of the East Asia region. The minister of international trade and industry, Datuk Sri Rafidah Aziz said in view of this there should be a greater network between the private sectors of both Malaysia and Czech. She noted that Malaysia is very interested to receive foreign direct investments in a broad range of activities. She said this at a meeting with the Foreign Minister of Czech Josef Zieleniec and his 35-member trade delegation at her ministry in Kuala Lumpur today. Datuk Sri Rafidah said bilateral trade of the two countries was only U.S.$20 million last year. She pointed out that the volume is very small and there is potential to expand it. Mr. Josef Zieleniec and the delegation are on a two-day visit to Malaysia. He called on the minister of foreign affairs, Datuk Abdullah Ahmad Badawi, at the Foreign Ministry in Kuala Lumpur this afternoon.
